[30;1m117 | [0m[35m## Version-String Flavors[0m
[30;1m118 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m119 | [0m[35mCode which uses Versioneer can learn about its version string at runtime by[0m
[30;1m120 | [0m[35mimporting `_version` from your main `__init__.py` file and running the[0m
[30;1m121 | [0m[35m`get_versions()` function. From the "outside" (e.g. in `setup.py`), you can[0m
[30;1m122 | [0m[35mimport the top-level `versioneer.py` and run `get_versions()`.[0m

[30;1m98 | [0m[35mtree, where your `__init__.py` can import it. This `_version.py` knows how to[0m

[30;1m102 | [0m[35mprocess marks `_version.py` to have this marker rewritten with a tag name[0m

[30;1m312 | [0m[35m    -----[0m
[30;1m313 | [0m[35m    You can use this config to limit the parallelism for the entire workflow[0m
[30;1m314 | [0m[35m    by setting the config at the very beginning.[0m
[30;1m315 | [0m[35m    >>> import modin.config as cfg[0m
[30;1m316 | [0m[35m    >>> cfg.RayTaskCustomResources.put({"special_hardware": 0.001})[0m
[30;1m317 | [0m[35m    This way each single remote task or actor will require 0.001 of "special_hardware" to run.[0m

[30;1m157 | [0m[35m        Perform the Map phase to compute the corr/cov matrix.[0m
[30;1m158 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m159 | [0m[35m        In this kernel we compute all the required components to compute[0m
[30;1m160 | [0m[35m        the correlation matrix at the reduce phase, the required components are:[0m
[30;1m161 | [0m[35m            1. Matrix holding sums of pairwise multiplications between all columns[0m
